LACE2 tana yaki da aikin enzyme mai sauya jini (ACE) ta hanyar rage yawan dangiotensin II da kuma kara lAng (1-7) wanda hakan ya sa ta zama wata babbar hanyar magani wajen maganin cututtukan zuciya da jijiyoyin jini. LACE2 kuma ita ce hanyar shigar wasu kwayoyin coronaviruses cikin kwayoyin.
An kira kwayar halitta ta mutum hACE2.
Langiotensin 2 mai sauya enzyme shine zinc-containing metallolenzime wanda yake a farfajiyar endothelial da sauran ƙwayoyin.
Kwayar ACE2 tana dauke da wani yanki na peptidase na M2 mai ƙare N da kuma wani yanki na collectrin mai ɗaukar amino acid na ƙwayoyin cuta mai ƙare C.
LACE2 shine mai wucewa guda ɗaya mai ɗaukar hoto mai nau'in I, wanda yankin aikinsa na enzymatic yana kan farfajiyar ƙwayoyin huhu da sauran kayan.
An cire yankin waje na ACE2 daga yankin transmembrane ta wani enzyme da ake kira sheddase; an saki furotin mai narkewa a cikin jini kuma a ƙarshe an cire shi cikin fitsari.
LACE2 tana cikin yawancin gabobin jiki: LACE2 tana haɗe da membrane na ƙwayoyin jiki, musamman na ƙwayoyin alveoli na huhu na nau'in II, ƙwayoyin enterocytes na ƙananan hanji, ƙwayoyin endothelial na arterial da na vein, da ƙwayoyin jini na tsokoki masu santsi na yawancin gabobin jiki.
Ana kuma bayyana mRNA na ACE2 a cikin cortex na kwakwalwa, striatum, hypothalamus da kuma ƙwaƙwalwar kwakwalwa.
Babban aikin ACE2 shi ne ya biya ACE.
ACE tana rarraba angiotensin I zuwa angiotensin II mai hana jini.
LACE2 kuma yana rarraba amino acid phenyllamine tare da ƙarshen carboxyl na angiotensin II (Asp-Arg-Val-Tyr-Ile-His-Pro-Phe) da kuma hydrolysis zuwa angiotensin mai yaduwa (1-7), (H-Asp-Arg-Val-Tyr-Ile-His-Pro-OH).
LACE2 na iya kuma tsage wasu peptides da dama ciki har da [des-Arg9]-bradykinin, lapelin, neurotensin, dynorphine A, da ghrelin.
LACE2 kuma tana daidaita yaduwar membrane na mai ɗaukar amino acid mai tsaka tsaki SLC6A19 kuma tana da hannu a cutar Hartnup.
A matsayin furotin mai wucewa ta membrane, ACE2 shine babban hanyar shiga cikin ƙwayoyin wasu ƙwayoyin cuta na coronavirus, ciki har da HCoV-NL63; SARS-CoV (kwayar cutar da ke haifar da SARS); da SARS-CoV-2 (kwayar cutar da ke haifar da COVID-19).
